@NODE Introduction_Node "NetProbe/Introduction"

    NetProbe is a statistic-gathering Tool for @{"Envoy" LINK Envoy_Node}.  One of it's main
    uses is to debug a network while trying to get it up and running.

    A @{"MUI" LINK Copyright_Node_MUI}- and a @{"shell" LINK shell_usage_NODE} version of NetProbe are available.

@ENDNODE


@NODE Concept_Node "NetProbe/Theory of operation"

    This program is based on the @{"NIPCInquiry" LINK NIPCInquiry_Node} function of nipc.library.

    The very first versions were created because I didn't want to recompile
    my little test programm *every* time I wanted to use a different set of
    scan tags.  Mainly,  NetProbe consists of a core of Envoy functions that
    start the NIPCInquiry function and build a linked list of the return
    packets and user-interface modules that let you select the set of tags
    for the next scan and show you the lists.

    Please note the @{"40.2-kludge" LINK Kludge_Node}.

@ENDNODE


@NODE NIPCInquiry_Node "NetProbe/nipc.library/NIPCInquiry"

    Excerpt from the nipc.library documentation:


    NAME
        NIPCInquiryA -- Start a nipc network query

    FUNCTION
        Starts an NIPC Network Inquiry.  This function can be used to gather
        data about a single machine,  or to gather data for a number of
        machines.  Multiple types of inquiries may be made using this
        function.  Please see below for a description of the types of queries
        and the types of information you may gather.

        ...

    For further information see the Envoy developer documentation on your
    Envoy disk(s).

@ENDNODE


@NODE mui_usage_Node "NetProbe/MUI Version"

    The main MUI window looks roughly like the following drawing:

    +------------------+----------------+--------------+----------+
    |                  |                |              |          |
    |    @{"Scan Realms" LINK Scan_Realms_Node}  |   @{"Scan Hosts" LINK Scan_Hosts_Node}   |   @{"Scan All" LINK Scan_All_Node}   |  @{"Quit" LINK Quit_Node}   |
    |                  |                |              |          |
    +------------------+----------------+--------------+----------+
    |                  |                |              |          |
    |            @{"Ping Host" LINK Scan_Ping_Node}              |      Host to ping       |
    |                  |                |              |          |
    +------------------+----------------+--------------+----------+
    |                                   |                         |
    |        @{"Realms  ListView" LINK Realms_ListView_Node}           |    @{"Services" LINK Services_Node}            |
    |                                   |                         |
    +-----------------------------------+-------------------------+
    |                                   |                         |
    |        @{"Hosts  ListView" LINK Hosts_ListView_Node}            |    @{"Entities" LINK Entities_Node}            |
    |                                   |                         |
    +-----------------------------------+-------------------------+
    |                                                             |
    |          Lots of @{"Checkboxes and Strings" LINK Strings_Node}                     |
    |                                                             |
    +-----------------------------------+-------------------------+


    Through the Menu,  you can access the following options:

        @{"About      " LINK About_Node       }
        @{"Save List  " LINK Save_List_Node   }
        @{"Preferences" LINK Preferences_Node }
        @{"Quit       " LINK Quit_Node        }

@ENDNODE


